sale of businesses in 2007 which did not repeat in 2008. accounts receivable
decreases benefited cash flows in 2008, but increases in inventories and
decreases in accounts payable negatively impacted cash flows. the category other-net
in the preceding table reflects changes in other asset and liability accounts,
