the global exposures related to purchased components and
materials are such that a 1 percent price change would result in a pre-tax cost
or savings of approximately $50 million per year. the global energy exposure is
such that a 10 percent price change would result in a pre-tax cost or savings
of approximately $37 million per year. derivative instruments are used to hedge
approximately 1 percent of the purchased components and materials exposure and
are used to hedge approximately 10 percent of this energy exposure.
